{meta: title Little Joe}
{meta: artist Hank Snow}
{meta: writer A.P. Carter, Maybelle Carter, Sara Carter}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]What will the birds do [F]mother in the [C]spring
[G7]When they stop to gather crumbs around the door
[C]Will they fly from the trees half as nice with [F]glee
[G7]Asking why Joe wanders out no [C]more
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[F]What will the kitten do mother all [C]alone
[G7]Will he stop from his frolic for the day
[C]Will he lie on his rug by the side of my [F]bed
[G7]As he did before I went [C]away
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[F]What will Thomas that old gardener [C]say
[G7]When you ask him for flowers for me
[C]Will he give you a rose he has tended with [F]care
[G7]The first fairest bloom of the [C]tree
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
[F]I have seen the tears in his honest old [C]eyes
[G7]But he said it was the wind that brought them there
[C]As he gazed on my cheeks growing paler each [F]day
[G7]And his hand went trembling through my [C]hair
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
[F]Keep tied mother my poor little [C]dog
[G7]For I know he'll mourn for me too
[C]Just keep him when old and useless he [F]grows
[G7]Sleeping the whole summer [C]through
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
[F]Show him my coat mother so he'll not [C]forget
[G7]His master who then will be dead
[C]Just speak to him kindly and often of [F]Joe
[G7]And pat him on his brown shaggy [C]head
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 7}
[F]And you dearest mother may miss me for a [C]while
[G7]But in heaven I'll no larger grow
[C]And any kind angel will know at the [F]gate
[G7]When you ask for your darling little [C]Joe
{end_of_verse}
